The evidence with the title 'Tax waste: 6.1 billion hours spent complying with federal tax code ' says Jan 5, 2011  ...  ... Taxpayers spend collecting data for and filling out each individual tax form by the number of forms filed to estimate that Americans ( both individuals and businesses ) spend 6.1 billion hours a year complying with the code . That's the equivalent of more than 3 million workers toiling away full time , all year. 
